  "lint_rules": "# lint_rules\nList all available lint rules with descriptions.\nToolset: lint\nWrite: no",
  "set_lint_ignore": "# set_lint_ignore\nSet lint rule exclusions on a specific node. Use to prevent specific lint rules from flagging a node (e.g. decorative elements that should not be treated as buttons). Pass rules as comma-separated names or \"*\" to exclude all rules. Pass empty string to clear.\nToolset: lint\nWrite: yes (access: edit)\n\nParams:\n  nodeId (string, required) — Node ID to set lint exclusion on\n  rules (string, required) — Comma-separated rule names to ignore (e.g. \"button-structure,wcag-target-size\") or \"*\" for all. Empty string to clear.",
  "lint_stats": "# lint_stats\nShow lint rule violation statistics for the current session. Tracks how often each rule triggers, helping identify which design patterns cause the most issues. Use to understand which rules need the most attention.\nToolset: lint\nWrite: no\n\nParams:\n  sortBy (frequency | name, optional) — Sort order: frequency (most violations first, default) or name (alphabetical)",
  "verify_design": "# verify_design\nCompound verification: runs lint_fix_all + export_image in a single call. Returns lint report and optional screenshot. Use after creating UI to verify quality and get a visual preview in one round-trip.\nToolset: core\nWrite: yes (access: create)\n\nParams:\n  nodeId (string, optional) — Node ID to verify (default: current page)\n  fix (boolean, optional) — Auto-fix violations (default: true)\n  exportImage (boolean, optional) — Include screenshot (default: true)\n  exportScale (number, optional) — Image scale factor (default: 0.5)",
  "compliance_report": "# compliance_report\nGenerate a comprehensive design system compliance report. Combines lint results, component audit, and token coverage into a single report.\nToolset: lint\nWrite: no\n\nParams:\n  nodeIds (array, optional) — Scope to specific nodes (default: entire page)\n  useStoredTokens (string, optional) — Name of cached token set for lint",
  "figma_login": "# figma_login\nStart Figma OAuth 2.0 login. Returns an authorization URL for the user to open in their browser. Requires FIGMA_CLIENT_ID env var.\nToolset: auth\nWrite: no",
